latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Presenting to you- @beyond.larissa ✨

Building this brand since 2 years has been nothing but a huge learning. Studying gemstones, gold and the process of jewellery making has been something that I was meant to do always. It’s like, I’ve found what I was made for ✨🤍

Since I was a kid, I have loved jewellery. Back then, it was chunky rings that I found at the local stores, and I would stack them all together…wear rings all literally all my fingers..because I saw Phoebe Buffay do it. You can say, she was my first inspiration to wear a lot of jewellery 😇

Since then, I have picked jewellery whenever I’ve travelled, made my own designs, I even made jewellery out of clay and sold them online on We Love Customade(my e-commerce store when I was 19), I have been obsessed!

In 2020, my passion for semi-precious and precious gemstones were ignited. I started wrapping Citrines and Amethysts in copper wires and wore them. And so many of my online audience noticed and asked me if I could make them commercially. 

That’s when I realised I wanted to get back to where it all began. Creating, executing, is what drives my creative force, so I studied and researched, about gemstones, about gold, started the process of designing my own designs just with mere visualisation. 

Gosh, it’s been a journey. This film was created at three different intervals by three different teams. 

✨Shot by: @nikophotoworld , @piyush_tanpure and @aishwaryaa.nayak .

✨Concept, Direction, post production: @larissa_wlc 

✨Narrated by : @el.halli 

✨Written by: @larissa_wlc 

#luxuryfinejewelry #luxejewels #jewellery #finejewellery #beyondlarissa

I had the honour to be a part of @youtubeindia’s Anthem 🤯 i shot for this Music video on the 3rd of January this year. #CreatingForIndia 

The Anthem stands for creators who bring about a change in peoples lives, and I couldn’t be more happy especially for the reason the anthem stands for🤍🙏🏼 

My ultimate goal is to give back as much as I receive and I hope i can “influence” you to do all the right things 🙏🏼🤍 annnddd travel 🥺

Loook at the set, this is SOOOO CUTE!!!! The set was only made for me, i couldnt believe my eyes🥺🥺🥺 i vlogged this day, would you want to watch? I wasnt allowed to post until the video was released so didn’t post yet..but if we have 100k views on this video, i will😌🙏🏼🤍 

Alsoo, in a music video with @jonitamusic ‘s voice 😍 🙏🏼

TRAVEL INFLUENCER OF THE YEAR - 2nd TIME IN A ROW!!! 

THIS IS SPECIFICALLY FOR MY FOLLOWERS😭😭😭😭 last year for me was burnout. A lot of personal things happened, and i couldnt do much with travel, EVEN AFTER i didnt travel much - just Jaipur, Maldives, Ladakh, Rishikesh, and exploring Goa - the last two years after the pandemic, for still trusting the quality…this literally makes me believe - QUALITY IS ALWAYS BETTER THAN QUANTITY. 

I did not expect this award. Not because i dont believe in myself, but because I never create content to win any award. Nor do I believe in making “viral” content, i only and only travel to share my experience with you, and very very subtly. Don’t get me wrong, viral content is also good content- but just not my style :) i believe in proving things quietly 😇

Butttt, little did i know that my audience- you all - even after only doing this much in covid times, you will STILLL BELIEVE, that i deserve it. HOWWWW MANN!!!!!!! My tears are only and only because TODAY i know our power as a community!!! I know how strong we can be. I know the potential of you all, and not just me. 

Thankyou!!!! And ofcourse i had it on camera!!! I had my accident on camera, how could i not have this🤣🤣🤣 

Also, congratulations to @anunaysood for sharing this award with me. It was lovely, and scarring 😅 (the man is nutsss!! But a funny kind) and i cannot wait to travel together with you and @wanderwithsky (like we promised each other 🤞🏽). Thankyou to @cosmoindia for sharing awards especially in the travel category because it matters to put out Women Travellers much more to break the stereotype 🙏🏼✨ 

Also, congratulating all my fellow nominees cuz travel can never be categorised. Every individual enjoys travel differently and i feel we all need awards not just me and anunay. @tanyakhanijow @bruisedpassports @aakritiranaofficial @shenaztreasury 🤍🤍🤍 we are all changing the way people look at travel and im proud of us🙏🏼

Thankyou @settlesubtle for capturing this🙏🏼🥺

VLOG COMING SOOONNN PIGLETSSSSSSS 😎😎😎😎

Welcome to Casa De Larsa 5.0 🪴

The theme for this home was: Jungle + Home-y + Travel! 🌸

So, I went ahead and created… JUNGLISSAA 🤪🌸
(Jungle + Larissa… get it?! 😜)

Tbh, I would’ve loved to have a balcony, a bigger space, and a little more breathing room.

But sometimes, life gives you ‘just enough’ to spark your creativity, to push you to use every bit of what you have and turn it into your own lovely little home. 🏠

Not everything ends with a full stop.
Some things just… shift.

This is the beginning of a new dawn: 
Where memory doesn’t weigh,
it whispers.
Where art doesn’t explain,
it invites. 👹

And where two people no longer fit the titles they once wore ☠️
so they stopped trying.
And that’s when grace slipped in.

We simply showed up,
as we are.
And let the space
do the talking.👽

Come experience it—Dali & Gala @daliandgala.blr 🦞
